{
  "texts": [
    "Liu et al. [110] proposed a terahertz all-dielectric metasurface absorber based on hybrid dielectric waveguide resonances.",
    "This research progress provides a new approach for controlling the emission and absorption of surface electromagnetic radiation.Traditional filters are designed based on the Fresnel formula and are composed of bulky multilayer dielectric films, which are not conducive to the application of filters in small integrated optical devices.",
    "Ghasemi [112] designed a metasurface based on concentric annular resonators, demonstrating the possibility of using metasurface structures for filter fabrication.",
    "Shen et al. [113] proposed and designed a dielectric metasurface filter composed of a silicon nano-disc array.",
    "This filter operates under the resonance excitation of electric dipoles."
  ]
}